    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="7">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six (6) retaining bolts and cover from the front bearing cover. Remove any
                remaining gasket material from the case and cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300754">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300754" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300754" filename="../figg13/G1300754.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Remove Cover From Front Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing retaining snap ring from the input shaft groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300755">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300755" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300755" filename="../figg13/G1300755.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Remove Bearing Retaining Snap Ring From Input Shaft Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the input shaft toward the case rear as far as possible.
                Pull the input shaft forward (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300756">Figure 56</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300756" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300756" filename="../figg13/G1300756.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Drive Input Shaft Toward Case Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pry bars or screwdrivers to complete removal of the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300757">Figures 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300757" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300757" filename="../figg13/G1300757.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Remove Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear spacer from the drive gear front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300757">Figure 57</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear internal snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300758">Figure 58</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300758" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300758" filename="../figg13/G1300758.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Remove Drive Gear Internal Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the input shaft forward and out of the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300759">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300759" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300759" filename="../figg13/G1300759.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Pull Input Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive gear from inside the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300759">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the bushing in the input shaft pocket and replace if necessary (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300760">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300760" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300760" filename="../figg13/G1300760.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Inspect Bushing in Input Shaft Pocket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
